      • checkColName

        private static java.lang.String checkColName(java.lang.String name)
        used to validate if the column name insert in the request is a valid column name of the csv. this method isn't case sensitive so if the column is "Nid" and the user write nid this function will return "Nid"
        Parameters:
        name - string of the column passed by spring
        Returns:
        the name of the column or null in case name isn't correct

      • stats

        static NumberStats stats(java.lang.String fieldName)
        used to calculate the statistics, based on NumberStats
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • checkFilterValidity

        private static boolean checkFilterValidity(java.lang.Object leftValue,
                                           java.lang.String operator,
                                           java.lang.Object rightValue)
        used to tell if the data passed to this function match the filter or not. it work both with String and int, but it will not consider the fields with a String array
        Parameters:
        leftValue - value of the column to compare at the value passed from postman
        operator - string that indicate the filter operation to do
        rightValue - value used to compare the data of the data-set
        Returns:
        the result of the filter

      • filter

        static java.util.Vector<DataCsvRow> filter(FilterParameter parameter)
        used to filter the data-set and return only the row that meet the condition of the input value and the operation. It use checkColName(String) to verify the correctness of the column name and the checkFilterValidity(Object, String, Object) to verify the condition
        Parameters:
        parameter - an object that contains operator, value and field name
        Returns:
        vector made by the data that met the conditions
